10. FORCE MAJEURE EXEMPTIONS: The vessels, their masters, and the Owner will not be held liable for any losses or damages that occur as a result of:

   a) The actions, negligence, or misconduct of the vessel's crew, including the captain, pilots, or other employees, during the operation or management of the vessel;
   b) Fires on board, unless caused by the intentional act or gross negligence of the Owner;
   c) Collisions, groundings, or other perils of navigable waters;
   d) Efforts to save life or property at sea;
   e) Losses or damages arising from inherent qualities or defects of the cargo;
   f) Any actions or omissions by the Charterer, the Owner, any other shipper, or consignee of the cargo, their agents or representatives;
   g) Inadequate marks on the cargo;
   h) Explosions, boiler failures, broken shafts, or any hidden defects in the vessel's hull, equipment, or machinery;
   i) The unseaworthiness of the vessel, unless due to lack of diligence by the Owner to maintain a seaworthy vessel, properly manned, equipped, and supplied;
   j) Any other events beyond the control of the Owner, including but not limited to: acts of nature, acts of war, hostilities, piracy, terrorism, seizure under legal process (with prompt provision of necessary bond), strikes, labor disputes, lockouts, stoppages or restraints of labor, or civil unrest.

